ledge file doesn't explicitly state—it just references the command-line arguments without clarifying what they're for. This is a minor omission since the reference is there, but the definition would help users understand the context better.\n\nI'm also noticing the knowledge file says setUpTable can only be empty, but the source specifies it could be either missing or empty—so there's a slight gap there. And for the groupId footnote, the source explains that using `default` means you want to use the default group ID without specifying one.\n\nNow I'm checking how the knowledge file handles the part about mixing default and individual group IDs. The source says both can be used together and both datasets remain valid, and the knowledge file captures this correctly, just more concisely.\n\nLooking at the section structure, the source has around 10 H2-level headings but the knowledge file only lists 6 sections, so there's a discrepancy in how comprehensively the content was organized. Looking at the RST structure, I'm seeing the H4 headings that sit under the H3 sections—things like データベースの準備, リクエストメッセージ, レスポンスメッセージ, and others related to test setup and verification. The automated check flagged 10 source headings versus 6 in the knowledge file, which suggests the V3 validation is counting both H2 and H3 levels. Now I'm checking whether テストデータの書き方 in the source is substantial enough—it has multiple subsections and runs quite long, so consolidating those H3 levels under the H2 might work if the section stays manageable. Let me verify if it meets the 2000 character threshold. I'm checking the character count for s5 against the validation rules—it comes in at about 31 characters, which falls below the 50-character threshold. But looking at the source material itself, this section is genuinely brief, so the short consolidation accurately reflects what's there rather than being an error. The V3 rules do call for flagging sections under 50 characters, though I need to clarify